interfaces.label: CollectorFetchContext
description:
The context for the `fetch` method: It includes the most commonly used clients in the collectors (ES and SO clients).
Both are scoped based on the request and the context:
- When users are requesting a sample of data, it is scoped to their role to avoid exposing data they shouldn't read
- When building the telemetry data payload to report to the remote cluster, the requests are scoped to the `kibana` internal user

interfaces.label: ICollector
description: Common interface for Usage and Stats Collectors

children.label: log
description: Logger

children.label: type
description: The registered type (aka name) of the collector

children.label: fetch
description:
The actual logic that reports the Usage collection.
It will be called on every collection request.
Whatever is returned in this method will be passed through as-is under
the {@link ICollector.type} key.

children.label: isReady
description: Should return `true` when it's safe to call the `fetch` method.

interfaces.label: ICollectorSet
description: Interface to register and manage Usage Collectors through a CollectorSet

children.label: makeUsageCollector
description:
Creates a usage collector to collect plugin telemetry data.
registerCollector must be called to connect the created collector with the service.

children.label: registerCollector
description:
Register a usage collector or a stats collector.
Used to connect the created collector to telemetry.

children.label: getCollectorByType
description: Returns a usage collector by type

interfaces.label: IUsageCounter
description:
Usage Counter allows to keep track of any events that occur.
By calling {@link IUsageCounter.incrementCounter} devs can notify this
API whenever the event happens.

children.label: domainId
description: Defines a domainId (aka a namespace) under which multiple counters can be stored

children.label: retentionPeriodDays
description:
Defines custom retention period for the counters under this domain.
This is the number of days worth of counters that must be kept in the system indices.
See USAGE_COUNTERS_KEEP_DOCS_FOR_DAYS for default value

children.label: incrementCounter
description: Notifies the counter about a new event happening so it can increase the count internally.

description: {@link IncrementCounterParams }
